[Claude]: Now I have a complete picture of the vulnerability. Let me submit all the findings.

The full attack chain is clear:
1. HTTP request comes in with `resourceName` extracted from path (e.g., `/javax.faces.resource/../WEB-INF/web.xml`) and `libraryName` from `?ln=` parameter
2. `isResourceIdentifierExcluded` only checks for file extensions (`.class`, `.jsp`, `.jspx`, `.properties`, `.xhtml`) - no path traversal check, no WEB-INF/META-INF check
3. `createResource` passes these directly to `ClassLoaderResourceLoader` which calls `ClassLoader.getResourceAsStream()` without sanitization
4. No WEB-INF/META-INF filtering in either `ClassLoaderResourceLoader` or `InternalClassLoaderResourceLoader`

